Inner Atlas use

For Inner Atlas, myth/religion should not override grounded analysis.

It should act as a late-stage interpretive layer, after the evidence layers.

Example:

Snapshot:
	•	neck pain
	•	poor sleep
	•	high stress
	•	recurring

Other layers say:
	•	biology: recovery compromised
	•	music: rhythm broken
	•	economics: energy overspent
	•	cybernetics: repeating loop

Myth layer might say:
	•	“This is a burden-bearing pattern”
	•	“The system is carrying weight at the shoulders/neck”
	•	“Recurring strain is becoming part of the user’s lived story”

That can help with:
	•	memory
	•	motivation
	•	adherence
	•	emotional resonance

But Mirror should always ensure it stays:
	•	non-literal
	•	non-coercive
	•	evidence-anchored

